== Survival ==
Survival has been defined as "the state or fact of continuing to live or exist especially in spite of difficult conditions" [http://beta.merriam-webster.com/interstitial-ad?next=/dictionary/survival]

[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Survivalism Survivalism] is a theory or movement of individuals and groups seeking to prepare for emergencies.  As such, the survival movement has generated and disseminated a wealth of information, much of it open source, in pursuit of survival in crisis conditions.

== Survivor Library ==
Created as a data base of documents to assist in the re-creation of a functioning society after a disaster, [http://www.survivorlibrary.com/ The Survivor Library] gathers together in digital pdf format a wealth of current as well as  historical documents.